<i>Posted by visionr on 05-24-2003 01:04 AM:</i>

<p><b> Calendar / Mob lists ?</b></p>

<p>I remember when I first started EQ bout 4 years back the Berthall was a very important place.  You came here to find out what guilds were available and how to contact them; what local news was happening within our community, and to view and or schedule events for your guild on the handy calender.  Most of this is still available to us, and I thank those have made it possible all these years.  Yet I feel theres a need for Bertoxxulous to come together and play the game Everquest with a sense of Harmony that has slowly disappeared since 1999, and I believe Berthall is the key to make that work. <br />
<br />
A lot of higher level guilds are competing with each other every day on EQ.  While some of the methods used to push a guild ahead are fair and just others appear to be shady or lack any kind of consideration for an entire guild of people who are trying to enjoy the game as well.  I've noticed other servers use mob lists and calendars to organize sets of mobs and cycles between guilds so that coexistance is possible between 2 3 or even 4 guilds who are at the same level in the game.<br />
<br />
I've noticed that recently the calendar for Hate was cut, and that worries me because those were the only zones in the game that were uncontested for a period of time.  You knew; if your guild was scheduled for Hate that day that it was yours and the community recognized that and respected it.  This allowed a guild authority to have greater focus on the workings of the raid, and a guild population to focus and work as a team.  <br />
<br />
Not having to worry about guild X steamrolling you is a comfortable feeling I assure you.<br />
<br />
There are some that think mob lists/calendars aren't possible in zones outside the planes due to the nature of the spawns, but I have seen it done and there is something to be learned.  If your clearing an entire zone only to turn around and do it 2 days later so that your rival guild doesn't excel any further then your not playing on Bertoxxulous.  I have always thought this to be a server where we the player characters fight together against the NPS's.  If you want to contest yourself, your class, race or guild against others that is by definition a PVP action; PVP servers are available.  Just because you can destroy a zone doesn't mean you should.  Two or three sets of yard trash and key mobs cycled between guilds in a competitive zone would allow the respect between those guilds to grow.  At the same time a complete set of spawns without fighting or tactless actions saves enough time to equip an entire guild over.<br />
<br />
Its not a matter of possibility; I've seen it work fluidly.  Its a matter of sacrafice that each guild suffer the loss, and work together to create a mutual respect between guilds that allows all to enjoy the game. I've seen Berthall publish this theme; its clearly shown in their efforts to create this community page.  Its where we come to catch up on community news, find a guild, and maybe post new ideas on what mob lists/calendars can do to make Bertoxxulous a better place to log-in.<br />
<br />
Its up to you all <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt=""> <br />
<br />
--mysteil <br />
65th wizard of Bertoxxulous<br />
<br />
<br />
(btw: I am member to no guild that demonstrates these actions.  My family, Deadly Sins, fell on its own accord for reasons totally separate.  It is in my search for a new guild that I saw this competition, and chose no "high level" guild at all rather than line myself up for battle with guild X in zones like Ssra.)<br />
<br />
Thank you</p>

